"{\"uid\": \"theconversation.com-olympics-2024-shows-the-untapped-potential-of-female-athletes-235734\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Lecturer in Sport and Fitness, The Open University  Senior Lecturer in Sport & Fitness, The Open University  The authors do not work for, consult, own shares in or receive funding from any company or organisation that would benefit from this article, and have disclosed no relevant affiliations beyond their academic appointment.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 329, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 88, \"end\": 107, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Open_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Open University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Open_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Open_University\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Open Universityprovides funding as a founding partner of The Conversation UK.\", \"from\": 333, \"to\": 414, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 394, \"end\": 413, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Conversation_(website)\", \"score\": 0.9999999999931788, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Conversation UK\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Conversation_(website)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Conversation_(website)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"View all partners  https://doi.org/10.64628/AB.dcm3ej3d5  Share article  Print article  With each Olympic Games athletes are expected to break new records.\", \"from\": 416, \"to\": 571, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sport science experts have beenspeculating for yearswhether we arereaching the limitsof human ability.\", \"from\": 572, \"to\": 674, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But they may be overlooking the fields where there is untapped potential: women's sports.\", \"from\": 675, \"to\": 764, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The rates of improvements in female athletic performanceappear to be exceedingthat of their male counterparts.\", \"from\": 766, \"to\": 876, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For example, between 1985-2004 the records of female marathon runners improved at a rate three times greater than men's.\", \"from\": 877, \"to\": 997, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This has led many people to question whether,despite a 10-12%performance gap in all distance sports, womenmay surpass menat endurance sports in the future.\", \"from\": 998, \"to\": 1153, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, due to inequalities in sport the profile, funding and research related to women's sport is lacking.\", \"from\": 1155, \"to\": 1263, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The charity Women in Sport suggest this \\\"reflects a wider bias within society\\\".\", \"from\": 1264, \"to\": 1343, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Out of \\u00a335 million the UK government invested into football the women's game received\\u00a33 millionin the 2022-23 financial year.\", \"from\": 1344, \"to\": 1469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1367, \"end\": 1380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_the_United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.999999109075758, \"rank\": 8.801073264738697e-07, \"text\": \"UK government\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_the_United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_the_United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Back in 2012 the UK-based Women's Sport and Fitness Foundation argued that women's sport was \\\"sidelined, underfunded and ignored\\\", with their research also suggesting that women's sport received only 0.5% of all commercial sponsorship.\", \"from\": 1471, \"to\": 1706, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Overten years laterthere remains a substantial funding gap.\", \"from\": 1707, \"to\": 1766, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A 2023 report commissioned by a woman's sport and entertainment collective which found that 90% of sponsorshipsstill go to men's sport.\", \"from\": 1767, \"to\": 1902, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And a 2023 study by Women in Sport found this lack of funding has a marked impact on career choices with less than29% of girlsand young women aged 13-24 saying they dream of reaching the top in sport compared to over 50% of boys and young men.\", \"from\": 1904, \"to\": 2147, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The report showed this can change with increased visibility of women's sport.\", \"from\": 2148, \"to\": 2225, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The number of girls who said they love sport and take part often rose from 50% in 2020 to 69% after theLionesses' Euro win in 2022.\", \"from\": 2226, \"to\": 2357, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The lack of money within women's sport not only affects athletes directly but also has other implications in terms of research and its application to performance.\", \"from\": 2359, \"to\": 2521, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Research advancements within sport have been pushing the boundaries of what is possible for the human body.\", \"from\": 2522, \"to\": 2629, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"New records in sport can often be attributed to thesport science advancementsthat help athletes to bolster their physical capabilities, aid recovery and rehabilitation and develop their mental strength.\", \"from\": 2630, \"to\": 2832, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But there is a major problem, nearly all of this research is focused on men with as little as6% of allsport research using female only participants.\", \"from\": 2834, \"to\": 2982, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The majority of stakeholders in positions of power within sport who make decisions arepredominantly mensuch as national governing bodies of sport, with control over where funding goes.\", \"from\": 2984, \"to\": 3168, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Of even greater concern is the fact that research conducted on men is being used toexplain female athletic performancewhen women are biologically, physiologically and psychologically different to men.\", \"from\": 3170, \"to\": 3370, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For example, research intoVO\\u2082 maxcapabilities (the maximum rate of oxygen your body can use during exercise) have allowed endurance athletes to reach performance feats previously thought to be impossible.\", \"from\": 3372, \"to\": 3576, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However most VO\\u2082 max research is based on men and little is known about sex differences.\", \"from\": 3577, \"to\": 3665, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Researchers in 2022, reviewing the evidence we do have of VO\\u2082 max differences between men and women, concluded that female athletes are being held back by a lack of scientific understanding of female physiology.\", \"from\": 3667, \"to\": 3878, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But with additional research and the development of more female specific approaches there is no telling the improvements that could be made to female performance.\", \"from\": 3880, \"to\": 4042, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For instance, the 2022 VO\\u2082 max review pointed to studies showing women have some advantages such as superiorfatigue resistance.\", \"from\": 4043, \"to\": 4170, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4066, \"end\": 4073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/VO2_max\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"VO\\u2082 max\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/VO2_max\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/VO2_max\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Researchers often point to the fact that studies with women have to control for more factors.Scientists have notedhow the fluctuations of hormones at different stages of the menstrual cycle as well as menstruation itself present complications when conducting research.\", \"from\": 4172, \"to\": 4440, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet, this challenge simply demonstrates how little we understand about female athletes.\", \"from\": 4441, \"to\": 4528, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sport as a career becomes even more difficult should female athletes wish to become mothers.\", \"from\": 4530, \"to\": 4622, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is particularly a problem in sports wherepeak performance age coincideswith peak fertility.\", \"from\": 4623, \"to\": 4719, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Research by one of the our team, (Candice Lingam-Willgoss), with several elite athletes who had become mothers during their elite careers and returned at the same level suggested there is alack of knowledgewithin sports when it came to supporting pregnant and post-partum athletes.\", \"from\": 4721, \"to\": 5002, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Traditionally this has resulted in many female athletes retiring before they have had the chance to reach their optimum performance.\", \"from\": 5003, \"to\": 5135, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Society does seem to be changing and six Team GB athleteswho are mothersare competing in the 2024 Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 5137, \"to\": 5249, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024 is the first Olympic Games toprovide a nurseryand accommodate breastfeeding athletes.\", \"from\": 5250, \"to\": 5346, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5250, \"end\": 5260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2403613560263914e-16, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And this year there areequal numbersof male and female athletes for the first time.\", \"from\": 5347, \"to\": 5430, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With more athletes talking about their experiences as mothers, such as Jessica Ennis-Hill andSerena Williams, it seems some progress is being made.\", \"from\": 5431, \"to\": 5578, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5502, \"end\": 5520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Ennis-Hill\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jessica Ennis-Hill\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Ennis-Hill\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Ennis-Hill\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read more:Does a woman's menstrual cycle affect her athletic performance?\", \"from\": 5580, \"to\": 5653, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's what the science says  We need to consider what is possible.\", \"from\": 5654, \"to\": 5721, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Talk at this year's Paris games has highlighted several female athletes who are likely tobreak records, including 200m sprinter Shericka Jackson from Jamaica tipped to break Flo-Jo's (Florence Griffith-Joyner) 36 year record.\", \"from\": 5723, \"to\": 5948, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5743, \"end\": 5748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999824850989639, \"rank\": 1.7515207642571947e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 5851, \"end\": 5867, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shericka_Jackson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shericka Jackson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shericka_Jackson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shericka_Jackson\"}, {\"begin\": 5873, \"end\": 5880, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9999999999904503, \"rank\": 4.738213151826483e-12, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Australian swimmer Kaylee McKeown has already set a new Olympic record for the 100 metre backstroke and Australian swimmerMollie O'Callaghanhas set a new 200m freestyle Olympic record.\", \"from\": 5949, \"to\": 6133, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5949, \"end\": 5959, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"score\": 0.9245318221966732, \"rank\": 0.08126989374341803, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\"}, {\"begin\": 5968, \"end\": 5982, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaylee McKeown\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\"}, {\"begin\": 6053, \"end\": 6063, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"score\": 0.9245318221966732, \"rank\": 0.08126989374341803, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Imagine what potential could be unlocked if we adopted female-centric approaches to training, recovery and mental preparation.\", \"from\": 6135, \"to\": 6261, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright \\u00a9 2010-2026,The Conversation Media Group Ltd\", \"from\": 6263, \"to\": 6317, \"entities\": []}]}"